1 Service Performance


When monitoring the status of the application services, it is import to retrieve the performance data in real-time and grasp the mutual relationship between each service transactions. A delay in transaction response time may have originated from not just that transaction but from a combination of all transaction’s resource bottleneck. JENNIFER provides following features in service monitoring.  

1.1 Transaction per second

Arrival Rate and Service Rate are the monitored information related with TPS (Transactions per Second). Arrival Rate identifies the number of service requests per second from users and Service Rate shows system’s throughput per second.  

This report is Service Rate.

#jui172112431764#


You can confirm the variation of Arrival Rate through Today’s Arrival Rate (tps), Recent Total Arrival Rate (tps) and Recent Arrival Rate per server (tps) chart by clicking [Real-time Monitoring]-[Throughput] menu.

1.2 Active Services

Jennifer monitors active services through the charts and active item tables such as speed bar, speed meter and the number of real-time active services. 

#jui932849822726#


1.3 Average Response Time

You can confirm the variation of response time through Today’s Average Response Time (sec)

#jui246542122524#


Average response time is determined by the elapsed time of the monitored server. Therefore, elapsed time between the client and server is not included in the average response time monitored by Jennifer. 

1.4 Hit Count


This data is the number of service per hour.

#jui045991303176#

2 How many users

We define system user concepts as visit user, who accessed the system even for a moment, active user, who asks service and concurrent user, who is using system not pressing enter key.

2.1 Visit Users per Hour

JENNIFER's visit user is counted in the business perspective. It shows how many people have interests about the site or the system in terms of business. Therefore,the visit user data does not stand for criteria of performance management. This report is summary data for visit user per hour.  

#jui158154262426#

2.2 Concurrent Users


How many people are using the website at any given moment? Concurrent User is important information for every website administrators and operations manager because the capacity of a system can be measured in terms of maximum concurrent users, at which point system performance begins to degrade noticeably if more users browse the website. Measuring concurrent user accurately and analyzing relationship between concurrent user count and system performance is necessary to ensure high-level service to users
